## Overview

Implement subtasks and card dependencies to reach 90% parity with Jira/Linear. These are the most requested PM features and essential for managing complex projects.

---

## Problem Statement

### Current Limitations

**Subtasks:**
- Tasks have checklists, but checklist items are just boolean checkboxes
- No way to track subtask details (description, priority, due date, assignee)
- Checklist items can't be filtered or sorted independently
- No way to see all subtasks across multiple cards

**Dependencies:**
- No way to mark that one task blocks another
- No visual indicators of blocked/blocking relationships
- No way to prevent moving blocked cards to "Done"
- No dependency graph visualization

### User Stories

**As a project manager:**
- I want to break large tasks into subtasks so I can track progress granularly
- I want to mark task dependencies so the team knows what's blocking what
- I want to see a dependency graph to identify bottlenecks

**As a developer:**
- I want to create subtasks for "Build authentication" (e.g., "Set up JWT", "Create login form", "Add password reset")
- I want to mark "Deploy to production" as blocked by "QA testing complete"
- I want to see all my subtasks in one view, not scattered across multiple cards

---

## Design Decisions

### Subtasks Architecture

**Option A: Upgrade Checklist Items to Full Tasks**
- **Pros:** Reuse existing checklist infrastructure, backward compatible
- **Cons:** Checklist items are simple booleans, would need major refactor

**Option B: Separate Subtask System**
- **Pros:** Clean separation, full task features (description, priority, etc.)
- **Cons:** More code, need migration path for existing checklists

**Decision: Option B** - Separate subtask system with richer data model.

### Subtask Data Model

```typescript
interface Subtask {
  id: string;
  parentTaskId: string;
  title: string;
  description?: string;
  completed: boolean;
  priority?: 'low' | 'medium' | 'high';
  dueDate?: string; // YYYY-MM-DD
  order: number; // For manual sorting
  createdAt: Date;
  completedAt?: Date;
}
```

**Storage:** Add `subtasks` array to Task interface, store in IndexedDB.

### Dependency Data Model

```typescript
interface TaskDependency {
  id: string;
  sourceTaskId: string; // Task that blocks
  targetTaskId: string; // Task that is blocked
  createdAt: Date;
}

interface Task {
  // ... existing fields
  dependencyIds: string[]; // Array of dependency IDs
}
```

**Storage:** Separate `dependencies` array in KanbanStore.

